I built an AI detective to find out why people quit their jobs.
By looking at satisfaction levels and work hours,
the AI can forecast if someone is about to leave."

The Technology
Python: The language.

Scikit-Learn: The pre-built brain library.

NumPy: For the heavy math.

Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP): The specific type of neural network.

The "Inner Workings"
I didn't just use a library; I also coded the Backpropagation math from scratch.
This includes the Sigmoid function to squish numbers and Derivatives to turn the 'Trust Knobs' (Weights) based on the error (Loss).

The Trainer (python1.py): It cleans the data, builds the 2-layer neural network $(6, 5)$, and trains the brain.
The Knowledge (hr_model.pkl): You have successfully "pickled" the brain. This is your most valuable file because it contains all the learning.
The Predictor (use_the_brain.py): A fast, separate script that loads the model and gives forecasts without needing the original 15,000-row Excel file.